---
/*
  On-brand teaching diagram for /wipe-laptop-soldered-storage.
  A soldered SSD cannot be removed, so you erase it in place: boot from a USB
  stick, run a firmware Purge on the soldered drive, get a certificate. Site
  palette + sans font; responsive inline SVG.
*/
---

<figure class="not-prose my-8">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 840 220"
    role="img"
    aria-label="Flow for wiping a soldered SSD in place: start from a laptop whose SSD is soldered to the board and cannot be removed, boot the laptop from a USB stick, run a NIST 800-88 firmware Purge on the drive where it sits, and receive a tamper-evident certificate. No disassembly."
    class="mx-auto block h-auto w-full max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-2"
    style="font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;"
  >
    <title>Boot from USB, firmware Purge the soldered drive in place, get a certificate, with no disassembly</title>

    <!-- Node 1: laptop with soldered SSD -->
    <g>
      <rect x="16" y="34" width="184" height="150" rx="14" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E4E8EE" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <!-- laptop -->
      <rect x="66" y="58" width="84" height="52" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <rect x="56" y="110" width="104" height="8" rx="3" fill="#5A6472" />
      <!-- soldered chip highlighted -->
      <rect x="92" y="72" width="32" height="24" rx="3" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <g stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.4">
        <line x1="92" y1="78" x2="86" y2="78" /><line x1="92" y1="90" x2="86" y2="90" />
        <line x1="124" y1="78" x2="130" y2="78" /><line x1="124" y1="90" x2="130" y2="90" />
      </g>
      <text x="108" y="88" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1E56E6">SSD</text>
      <text x="108" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">Soldered SSD</text>
      <text x="108" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" fill="#5A6472">cannot be removed</text>
    </g>

    <!-- Node 2: boot from USB -->
    <g>
      <rect x="230" y="34" width="184" height="150" rx="14" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E4E8EE" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <rect x="300" y="60" width="26" height="46" rx="4" fill="#3E7BFA" />
      <rect x="308" y="48" width="10" height="14" rx="2" fill="#5A6472" />
      <text x="322" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">Boot from</text>
      <text x="322" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">USB stick</text>
    </g>

    <!-- Node 3: firmware Purge in place -->
    <g>
      <rect x="444" y="34" width="184" height="150" rx="14" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E4E8EE" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <rect x="500" y="64" width="72" height="42" rx="6" fill="#EAF1FF" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <path d="M528 76 a12 12 0 1 1 -8 4" fill="none" stroke="#3E7BFA" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" />
      <path d="M518 78 l3 -8 l7 5 z" fill="#3E7BFA" />
      <text x="536" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">Firmware Purge</text>
      <text x="536" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" fill="#5A6472">in place</text>
    </g>

    <!-- Node 4: certificate -->
    <g>
      <rect x="658" y="34" width="166" height="150" rx="14" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E4E8EE" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <rect x="712" y="58" width="58" height="50" rx="5" fill="#F4F6F9" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.5" />
      <line x1="722" y1="70" x2="760" y2="70" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <line x1="722" y1="80" x2="760" y2="80" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <line x1="722" y1="90" x2="748" y2="90" stroke="#5A6472" stroke-width="1.4" />
      <circle cx="766" cy="102" r="12" fill="#158048" />
      <path d="M760 102 l4 4 l7 -9" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
      <text x="741" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="600" fill="#141922">Certificate</text>
      <text x="741" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" fill="#5A6472">tamper-evident</text>
    </g>

    <!-- arrows -->
    <g fill="#3E7BFA">
      <path d="M208 102 l14 7 l-14 7 z" />
      <path d="M422 102 l14 7 l-14 7 z" />
      <path d="M636 102 l14 7 l-14 7 z" />
    </g>
  </svg>
  <figcaption class="mt-3 text-center text-sm text-muted">
    You erase a soldered drive where it sits: no disassembly, no shredding, just a verified wipe and
    a certificate.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
